description:
&lt;p&gt;Cardiff and Vale University Health Board Community Dietetic service is recruiting a band 6 dietitian to support it&#39;s work with targeted communities to tackle health inequalities. You will be part of the public health dietetic team consisting of dietitians and support workers. You will be working with people and communities across the life course, developing skills and knowledge through a community development approach including delivery of the Nutrition Skills For Life Programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working in public health and delivery of Nutrition Skills for Life is an advantage for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Community Dietetic Service is part of an integrated health board wide service. There are excellent links with primary care, Community Resource Service, the local public health team, local authority and third sector organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This UHB is a trainer of student dietitians and you will be required to input into this training program. This role may include some evening and weekend work and involves travelling around Cardiff and Vale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate that they share our organisational values in line with Caring for People: Keeping People Well:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-We care about the people we serve and the people we work&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-We trust one another&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-We respect each other&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-We take personal responsibility&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-We treat people with kindness&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-We act with integrity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 9th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Emma Holmes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Public Health Dietetic Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: emma.holmes@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 02920907699&lt;/p&gt;
